    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Minister in Saudi Arabia (
                        Eddy
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d887</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">887</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-11T01:54:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-11T01:54:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-11T01:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-11T01:54:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.248/6–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-11T10:00:00+03:06">June 11, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>235. Re Dept’s 156, June 5.<note n="24" xml:id="d887fn24">Same as telegram 1151,
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> King Abdul Aziz has telegraphed
                    that he agrees to postponement of my visit to Riyadh as he wishes <pb facs="0917" n="905" xml:id="pg_905"/> negotiations to be comprehensive
                    including all proposals of US Govt in Saudi Arabia. He expects to hear from me
                    before the end of June officially on the matters broached to him tentatively in
                    Dept’s 131, May 7.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
